Following are the major news items in leading British newspapers today: The
Times: -- The British and Irish governments have drawn up a document that
brings the prospect of a united Ireland closer than it has been at any time
since partition in 1920. Financial Times: -- Sir Leon Brittan, EU external
relations commissioner, yesterday called for a rethink of the relationship
between the EU and the U.S., saying that good EU-U.S.  relations were
necessary to develop the global trading system. The Guardian: -- Up to a
quarter of a million people in the eastern Netherlands abandoned their
homes yesterday as ever-rising water level threatened to breach dikes. The
Daily Telegraph: -- Moscow acknowledged yesterday that repeated warning of
a final assault on the remaining Chechen-held areas of Grozny have failed
to scare off the defenders.
